fields.name: ApiRevision
fields.description: Describes the revision of the API. If no value is provided, default revision 1 is created

fields.name: ApiRevisionDescription
fields.description: Description of the API Revision.

fields.name: ApiVersion
fields.description: Indicates the version identifier of the API if the API is versioned

fields.name: ApiVersionDescription
fields.description: Description of the API Version.

fields.name: ApiVersionSet
fields.description: Version set details

fields.name: ApiVersionSetId
fields.description: A resource identifier for the related ApiVersionSet.

fields.name: AuthenticationSettings
fields.description: Collection of authentication settings included into this API.

fields.name: Contact
fields.description: Contact information for the API.

fields.name: Description
fields.description: Description of the API. May include HTML formatting tags.

fields.name: DisplayName
fields.description: API name. Must be 1 to 300 characters long.

fields.name: IsCurrent
fields.description: Indicates if API revision is current api revision.

fields.name: IsOnline
fields.description: Indicates if API revision is accessible via the gateway.

fields.name: License
fields.description: License information for the API.

fields.name: Path
fields.description: Relative URL uniquely identifying this API and all of its resource paths within the API Management service instance. It is appended to the API endpoint base URL specified during the service instance creation to form a public URL for this API.

fields.name: Protocols
fields.description: Describes on which protocols the operations in this API can be invoked.

fields.name: ServiceUrl
fields.description: Absolute URL of the backend service implementing this API. Cannot be more than 2000 characters long.

fields.name: SourceApiId
fields.description: API identifier of the source API.

fields.name: SubscriptionKeyParameterNames
fields.description: Protocols over which API is made available.

fields.name: SubscriptionRequired
fields.description: Specifies whether an API or Product subscription is required for accessing the API.

fields.name: TermsOfServiceUrl
fields.description: A URL to the Terms of Service for the API. MUST be in the format of a URL.

fields.name: Type
fields.description: Type of API.
